      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(codex): continue after post-tool progress-only harness turns",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis patch fixes a Codex Harness truncation mode observed in OpenClaw 5.28 replay runs: after tool activity, the embedded runner can accept a progress-only assistant message as the final response when the model stops with `stop`. In the affected runs the final visible text was not a delivery summary, but a next-step announcement such as:\n\n- `Now let me create the sample logs ...`\n- `Now the Flask server with all API endpoints.`\n\nWhen this happens, the judge sees an incomplete workspace even though the assistant text indicates more concrete work should follow.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Add post-tool continuation detection for progress-only assistant text in the incomplete-turn logic.\n- When the condition is met, inject a one-time continuation retry instruction into the embedded runner path so the agent continues from the current transcript instead of stopping early.\n- Keep the behavior scoped to Codex/OpenAI response-family paths with prior tool activity.\n- Expose `plugins.entries.codex.config.appServer.turnAssistantCompletionIdleTimeoutMs` through the Codex plugin config and manifest so the assistant completion idle timeout is configurable without patching built runtime output.\n- Add resolver-level and runner-level regression coverage.\n\n## Validation\n\nLocally passed:\n\n```text\npnpm exec vitest run src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run.incomplete-turn.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/config.test.ts\nTest Files  3 passed (3)\nTests       311 passed (311)\n```\n\nAlso passed:\n\n```text\ngit diff --check HEAD^..HEAD\nnode scripts/check-plugin-npm-runtime-builds.mjs --package extensions/codex\nbuilt 1 publishable plugin runtimes\ncodex  8  -\n```\n\n## Replay context\n\nThe issue was identified from a four-group OpenClaw 5.28 replay comparing Codex Harness, Codex ACP, Codex Harness with agent workspace, and OpenClaw PiAgent. Two Harness cases stopped after only 6 tool rounds with progress-only final assistant text, leading to low judge scores on the affected tasks.\n\nA full patched leaf re-run against the external Ark/DeepSeek route is not included in this PR because the current execution environment does not have `ARK_API_KEY`. The included runner-level regression test verifies that the embedded runner enters a second attempt after the same class of post-tool progress-only response.\n\n## CPU note\n\nThe same replay showed higher local CPU time for Harness than ACP. The current root-cause assessment is that this comes from the local embedded runner, Codex app-server runtime, session/trajectory mirroring, dynamic tool bridge, and archival writes. This patch addresses the correctness bug that caused early truncation; it intentionally does not bundle broader CPU optimization work.\n",
        "branch": "fix/codex-harness-post-tool-continuation",
